This paper is about off-road autonomous vehicles, which falls under the robotics (RO) category. The paper proposes a method of off-road traversability analysis and trajectory planning using Deep Maximum Entropy Inverse Reinforcement Learning, which involves machine learning (LG) and computer vision (CV) techniques. The paper also mentions the use of behavior-based methods, which is a subfield of artificial intelligence (AI). Finally, the paper discusses the incorporation of vehicle kinematics, which is related to control systems (SY). Therefore, the most likely sub-category is cs.RO, followed by cs.LG, cs.CV, cs.AI, and cs.SY.
